examples.en: He blew his chance.
My ticket blew away.
The plan blew up in his face.
He blew his nose noisily.
He blew $50 on lunch.
The March wind blew in chilly.
The heat blew out the tyre.
The wind blew from the east.
The wind blew from the south.
Her umbrella blew inside out.
She blew onto her coffee to cool it down.
examples.ru: Она подула на свой кофе, чтобы остудить.

examples.en: We blew them out 28—0.
The company blew in $52,000.
examples.ru: Руководство компании пустило на ветер пятьдесят две тысячи долларов.

examples.en: He nearly blew us to kingdom come.
examples.ru: Он чуть не взорвал нас к чёртовой матери.

examples.en: He blew heavily through his nostrils.
A biting wind blew down from the hills.
The wind blew the door to.
The floodlights blew a fuse.
The plane blew up in mid-air.
He blew a whiff from his pipe.
Jim blew in about an hour ago.
examples.ru: Джим заявился сюда около часа назад.

examples.en: The bomb blew the windows out.
The whistle blew for halftime.
The policeman blew his whistle.
A damp wind blew from the west.
The lifeguard blew his whistle.
The match blew out in the wind.
examples.ru: Спичка потухла на ветру. / Ветер задул спичку.

examples.en: Our fence blew over in the storm.
The explosion blew the door open.
The wind blew from the northeast.
